The paper discusses the use of machine learning in automotive software development, specifically in the context of safety. This suggests that the paper is likely to fall under the Software Engineering (cs.SE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the application of supervised learning, which is a subfield of Machine Learning (cs.LG), and the use of ML in Automated Driving Systems (ADS), which falls under Robotics (cs.RO).
